Any immunoglobulin that recognizes type V collagen.
Any immunoglobulin that recognizes tubulin alpha-1B chain protein.
An infectious process caused by adenovirus. The virus may cause respiratory illness, conjunctivitis, gastroenteritis, and cystitis.
Grade III lymphomatoid granulomatosis that occurs in adulthood.
Any immunoglobulin that recognizes baculoviral IAP repeat-containing protein 5.
Narrowing of the lumen of an artery or vein.
Myelodysplastic syndrome that occurs in adulthood.

value.value: Nasal type extranodal NK/T-cell lymphoma that occurs in adulthood.
Any immunoglobulin that recognizes cellular tumor antigen p53 protein.
Any immunoglobulin that recognizes melanoma-associated antigen 3 protein.
Fibrosis of the skin, joints and other organs usually associated with gadolinium exposure in the setting of kidney failure.
Any immunoglobulin that recognizes melanocyte protein PMEL.
Sudden increase of the number of blasts in the bone marrow and/or peripheral blood in a patient with a history of chronic leukemia.
Malposition of a peritoneal dialysis catheter.
Malposition and dysfunction of a peritoneal dialysis catheter.
Pneumonia that is not acquired in a hospital or long-term care facility setting.
An infection acquired in a hospital or other healthcare setting.
Inflammation of the salivary glands.
This gene plays a role in feeding behavior.

Human AGRP wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 16q22 and is approximately 1 kb in length. This allele, which encodes agouti-related protein, is involved in the regulation of feeding behavior. Mutation of the gene is associated with obesity.
Rupture in the bladder wall due to a pathologic process, in the absence of trauma.
Agouti-related protein (132 aa, ~14 kDa) is encoded by the human AGRP gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of feeding behavior.
This gene is involved in gap junction assembly.

Human GJA1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6q22.31 and is approximately 14 kb in length. This allele, which encodes gap junction alpha-1 protein, plays a role in the modulation of the activity of gap junctions. Mutation of the gene is associated with atrioventricular septal defect 3, autosomal recessive craniometaphyseal dysplasia, hypoplastic left heart syndrome 1, oculodentodigital dysplasia and syndactyly, type III.
Gap junction alpha-1 protein (382 aa, ~43 kDa) is encoded by the human GJA1 gene. This protein is involved in the regulation of the assembly of gap junctions.
This gene plays a role in chloride transport.

Human ANO1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11q13.3 and is approximately 111 kb in length. This allele, which encodes anoctamin-1 protein, is involved in the modulation of chloride transport.
Anoctamin-1 (986 aa, ~114 kDa) is encoded by the human ANO1 gene. This protein plays a role in calcium-dependent transport of chloride.
This gene is involved in protein hydrolysis.

Human CELA1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12q13 and is approximately 18 kb in length. This allele, which encodes chymotrypsin-like elastase family member 1 protein, plays a role in the mediation of proteolysis.
Chymotrypsin-like elastase family member 1 (258 aa, ~28 kDa) is encoded by the human CELA1 gene. This protein is involved in protein hydrolysis.
This gene plays a role in catalyzing protein folding.

Human PPIB wild-type allele is located within 15q21-q22 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes peptidyl-prolyl cis-trans isomerase B protein, is involved in protein folding. Mutation of the gene is associated with osteogenesis imperfecta type 9.
Peptidyl-prolyl cis-trans isomerase B (216 aa, ~24 kDa) is encoded by the human PPIB gene. This protein plays a role in the mediation of protein folding.
This gene is involved in the storage of coagulation factor V/Va in platelets.

Human MMRN1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q22 and is approximately 75 kb in length. This allele, which encodes multimerin-1 protein, plays a role in platelet factor V/Va homeostasis.
Multimerin-1 (1228 aa, ~138 kDa) is encoded by the human MMRN1 gene. This protein is involved in stabilization of platelet-bound factor V/Va.
This gene plays a role in the lubrication of mucosal surfaces.

Human MUC2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11p15.5 and is approximately 30 kb in length. This allele, which encodes mucin-2 protein, is involved in preventing irritation of mucosal surfaces.
Mucin-2 (5179 aa, ~540 kDa) is encoded by the human MUC2 gene. This protein plays a role in coating the intestinal epithelium.
This gene is involved in the inhibition of both gastric acid secretion and gastrointestinal motility.

Human TFF2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 21q22.3 and is approximately 5 kb in length. This allele, which encodes trefoil factor 2 protein, plays a role in both gastrointestinal motility and gastric acid secretion.
Trefoil factor 2 (129 aa, ~14 kDa) is encoded by the human TFF2 gene. This protein is involved in the negative regulation of gastrointestinal motility and gastric acid secretion.
This gene plays a role in microtubule assembly and disassembly.
